In [6]:
def scatter_label(data, labels, numPoints = 300):
    
    numEntries = data.shape[0]
    start = rand.randint(0, numEntries - numPoints)
    end = start + numPoints
    data = data.iloc[start:end, :]
    labels = labels.iloc[start:end]
    
    mds = MDS(n_components=2)
    mds_data = mds.fit_transform(data.iloc[:, :-1])
    plt.scatter(mds_data[:, 0], mds_data[:, 1],c=labels, s=50)
    plt.show()
In [7]:
def scatter_nolabel(data, numPoints = 300):
    
    numEntries = data.shape[0]
    start = rand.randint(0, numEntries - numPoints)
    end = start + numPoints
    data = data.iloc[start:end, :]
    
    mds = MDS(n_components=2)
    mds_data = mds.fit_transform(data.iloc[:, :-1])
    plt.scatter(mds_data[:, 0], mds_data[:, 1], s=50)
    plt.show()

We decided to visualize our missing values for each column. This revealed the large number of missing values for both "Armed" and "Race". Because of this, we proposed to create three separate clusters: one with all of the race values, one with all of the armed values, and one complete dataset with the Race and Armed rows taken out all together.

Hot encoding categorical feature¶

Features such as Gender, Race, Manner of death, Armed, Mental Illness and Flee

In [17]:
datasets = [data, data_armed, data_race]

for i in range(len(datasets)):
    dataset = datasets[i]
    features = ["Race", "Mental_illness", "Armed", "Flee",  "Manner_of_death", "Gender"]
    for f in features:
        try:
            col = dataset[f]
            col = pd.Categorical(col)
            encoded = pd.get_dummies(col, prefix=f)
            dataset = pd.concat([dataset, encoded], axis=1)
            dataset = dataset.drop(f, axis=1)
        except:
            continue
    datasets[i] = dataset

for d in datasets:
    print(d.shape)

Isolating data from California.

ca_datasets = []
for i in range(len(datasets)):
    dataset = datasets[i]
    ca_data = dataset[dataset["State"] == "CA"].copy()
    ca_data = ca_data.drop("State", axis=1)
    ca_datasets.append(ca_data)

data, data_armed, data_race = ca_datasets
print("Data shape:", data.shape)
print("Data Armed shape:",data_armed.shape)

Feature Engineering¶

Feature reduction using PCA

In [20]:
for i in range(len(ca_datasets)):
    ca_data = ca_datasets[i]
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(ca_data)
    pca = PCA(n_components=0.9995, svd_solver='full')
    pca_data = pca.fit_transform(scaled_data)

    ca_data = DataFrame(pca_data)
    ca_datasets[i] = ca_data

data, data_armed, data_race = ca_datasets
print("Data shape:", data.shape)
print("Data Armed shape:",data_armed.shape)
print("Data Race shape:",data_race.shape)

Data shape: (2863, 17)
Data Armed shape: (2863, 11)
Data Race shape: (2863, 13)

DBScan¶

Estimate the Eps based on the distance from 4th nearest neighbor

In [22]:
for ca_data in ca_datasets:
    nn = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=4)
    nn.fit(ca_data)
    distances = nn.kneighbors()[0]
    fourth_distances = []

    for d in distances:
        fourth_distances.append(d[-1])
    fourth_distances.sort()

    plt.plot(fourth_distances)
    plt.show()
In [23]:
dbscan = DBSCAN(min_samples=6, eps=7.5)
